  <refsect1>
    <title>Description</title>
    <para>Basic module component interface that all user implemented modules must implement. </para>
    <para> The function <literal><link linkend="METHOD-13-3">vidis.data.mod.IUserComponent.execute</link></literal> is called by the simulator at each simulation step. </para>
  </refsect1>
  <refsect1>
    <title>Methods</title>
    <refsect2 xml:id="METHOD-13-3" xreflabel="execute()">
      <title>execute()</title>
      <indexterm><primary>execute</primary></indexterm>
      <indexterm><primary>Methods</primary><secondary>execute</secondary></indexterm>
      <methodsynopsis language="java">
        <modifier>public</modifier>
        <type>void</type>
        <methodname>execute</methodname>
        <void/>
      </methodsynopsis>
      <para>Is executed on each simulation step. </para>
      <itemizedlist><listitem>
         Hint: it is impossible to tell which of the components executes first!
        </listitem>
<listitem>
          Hint: do NOT use Thread.sleep() or something like that - it will only hang the simulator
        </listitem>
<listitem>
          Hint: use built-in sleep() and interrupt() functions!
        </listitem>
</itemizedlist>
    </refsect2>
    <refsect2 xml:id="METHOD-13-1" xreflabel="getVariable(java.lang.String)">
      <title>getVariable(String)</title>
